<paragraph id="8BD136A7FFC8FFA3D4CCF9EC09FCF859" blockId="53.[151,1437,1607,2030]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFC8FFA3D4CCF9EC0C43F9F2" box="[199,283,1607,1633]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Female</emphasis>
(IAvH-I-3765). Coloration, abdominal and spots pattern as male (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFC8FFA3D01EF9EC09F9F9F1" box="[1045,1185,1607,1634]" captionStart="FIGURE 35" captionStartId="54.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[257,1331,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-27@54.[257,1331,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 35. Tenedos peckorum Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002. A–B. Male habitus (MPUJ_ENT 0070625): A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–D. Female habitus (IAvH-I-3765): C. Dorsal view. D. Ventral view. Scale bar: A–D: 2.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520852" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520852/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Fig. 35C–D</figureCitation>
). Measurements: total length 9.10, carapace length 4.33, width 2.56, height 2.02. Clypeus height 0.94. Eye diameters and interdistances: AME 0.12, ALE 0.17, PME 0.12, PLE 0.20; AME–AME 0.28, AME–ALE 0.37, AME–PME 0.38, PME–PME 0.37, PME–PLE 0.61, ALE–PLE 0.41. Chelicerae 1.78 length. Sternum length 1.57, width 1.60. Legs: I—femur 2.64/ patella 1.01/ tibia 2.39/ metatarsus 2.24/ tarsus 1.56/ total 7.79; II—2.28/ 1.05/ 2.09/ 2.11/ 1.34/ 6.58; III—2.25/ 1.04/ 1.71/ 2.41/ 1.24/ 6.52; IV—2.66/ 1.11/ 2.49/ 2.85/ 1.05/ 8.50. Abdomen length 4.24. Legs spines pattern (only the differences from the general pattern): I—tibia v2-1r-2, metatarsus v2-2-2, p0-0-1v; II—tibia v1p-2-2 (10), r0- 0-1p, p01d-1d. Epigyne: lateral borders (LB) short, restricted to posterior region; atrium (A) rectangular; median field plate large, rounded at basal edge; copulatory ducts (CD) short, thin; seminal receptacles (SR) long, thin, with rounded protuberance on base, curved towards median septum; spermathecae (S) large, rounded, medially positioned; fertilization ducts (FD) almost as long as spermathecae length (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFC8FFA3D7BBF804096FF85A" box="[944,1079,1967,1993]" captionStart="FIGURE 36" captionStartId="55.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[240,1348,189,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-19@55.[240,1348,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="FIGURE 36. Tenedos peckorum Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002. A–D. Male palp (MPUJ_ENT 0070625): A. Prolateral view. B. Retroventral view. C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. E–F. Female epigyne (IAvH-I-3765): C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–D: 300µm; E–F: 200µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520854" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520854/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Figs 36E–F</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFC8FFA3D048F81B09C0F859" box="[1091,1176,1968,1994]" captionStart="FIGURE 37" captionStartId="56.[151,250,1505,1529]" captionTargetBox="[161,1436,186,1470]" captionTargetId="figure-27@56.[151,1436,181,1481]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURE 37. Tenedos peckorum Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002. A–B. Male palp (MPUJ_ENT 0070625): A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. C–D. Female epigyne (IAvH-I-3765): C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm. Abbreviations: aMA, anterior branch of the median apophysis; C, conductor; CD, copulatory ducts; FD, fertilization ducts; pRTA, posterior branch of the retrolateral tibial apophysis; pMA, posterior branch of the median apophysis; MFP, median field plate; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520858" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520858/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">37C–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
